1. Open Templates
2. Duplicate Web Server template
3. Choose Windows Server 2008 under 'Certificate Authority"
4. Click "General" Tab
5. Change "Template display name" .... vSphere 6.0
6. click "Extensions" Tab
7. Highlight "Application Policies" and click "edit"
8. Slect "Server Authentication" and remove
9. Click "ok"
10. Select "Key Usage" and click "edit"
11. Click "Signature is proof of origin" leave everything else as default and click "ok"
12. Click "Subject Name" Tab
13. Confirm "Supply in the request" is selected
14. Click "ok" to save the template
